      "summary": "Wine descriptions are often the part that most intimidates beginners, filled with words like tannic, acidic, full-bodied, minerally, or finish that seem to require years of tasting experience to understand. They do not. Each of these words describes a specific physical sensation or flavor quality that you can learn to recognize and use as a practical decision-making tool. This concept teaches you the key flavor dimensions of wine, what each one feels like in the glass, and how to use them together to compare options on any wine list.",
